    "kstables": "Excluded per chain: the market-maker operational wallet and all 38 auto-convert vault balances of the queried coin.",
    "deposits": "G10 term deposits: when a kStable is deposited into a DiscountBill it moves from the depositor into the issuer-custodied deposit Treasury (exclusion label g10-deposit-treasury) and the depositor receives a bill NFT \u2014 a redemption claim, NOT a circulating kStable. The deposited kStable is therefore out of circulation and correctly excluded. That same Treasury also holds the PRE-MINTED 5%-of-supply interest reserve, so a bill's future interest is already in totalSupply and already excluded from circulating; at redemption the face (principal + interest) is TRANSFERRED (never minted) from the Treasury to the holder. totalSupply is invariant across deposit -> accrue -> redeem; circulating changes only when tokens cross the excluded/public boundary. A house deposit (MM wallet -> Treasury) leaves circulating unchanged (both excluded); a customer deposit lowers circulating and a customer redemption raises it by the face. The DiscountBill contract is also excluded defensively. Full treatment + reconciliation in docs/SUPPLY_DEPOSITS.md.",
    "lpPositions": "LP-manager protocol-owned pool positions are NOT yet excluded in v1 (they sit inside pool contracts, not in wallet balances). This diverges from the INSTITUTIONAL_ACCEPTANCE \u00a7E target exclusion list; the append-only exclusion registry (\u00a7E item E2) will add them. Until then the published kStable circulating figure is an upper bound on that one dimension.",
    "eigencarbon": "No exclusions yet \u2014 treasury-held addresses pending owner identification; circulating == totalSupply until then."
